metadata.name: Unfolded #229
metadata.description:
A plane is repeatedly folded over itself, choosing creases either at random, or according to some pattern (like a grid). These creases form the boundaries of the individual textured tiles.

Once the folds are complete, they are undone in reverse order, recreating the original plane. With each unfolding, the orientation of each crease (as a mountain or a valley), and each tile (facing up or down) is recorded as a sequence of 1s and 0s. Tiles are colored and textured according to similarities in these binary sequences, giving rise to subtle symmetries and repetitions.

Written in vanilla JS & HTML5 Canvas.

metadata.name: Patched and Mended #38
metadata.description:
My previous Token "Patched" had an issue where different viewport sizes rendered slightly different outputs. At the time I was not able to correct this but now I am!
Patched and Mended has different palettes from the original, including a monochrome version, and doesn't have a resizing issue.
This is an airdrop and I have reserved all of the pieces allocating them to the current holders of Patched. When I added them all up there was one missing so I have allocated that to myself and if anyone finds they don't have an allocation do let me know and I'll hand it over.

metadata.name: AutomataPunk, The Masquerader #64
metadata.description:
A playful spin on PFPs, and the prevalence of them on social media, especially among the NFT community.
The characters are procedurally generated, and then colored and texturized using 1D Cellular Automata.
Masqueraders hide their rarity scores. The cutest or most unusual one will be the most popular.
Their dimensions are always a multiple of 360.

Controls:
- Press 's' to save a PNG file.
- Press 't' to toggle, for a larger and higher resolution version that once complete can be saved as a 3600x3600 PNG by pressing 's'. In this mode, the Masquerader may become much larger than your screen. Wait for its render to complete before saving it. Toggle back to the regular size by pressing 't' again.

License:
See included LICENSE.md

Credits:
Made in p5js

metadata.name: Bamboo #11
metadata.description:
During my childhood we had a small patch of bamboo in our backyard. 
I fondly remember playing with the hollow sticks but also cutting myself on the fibrous leaves.
"Bamboo" aims to capture the adventures I would envision while looking at that small jungle in my garden.

Inspiration was drawn from pointillism, botanical illustration and naive art.

The piece is purely generative, in the sense of painting the picture with code via p5js points and shapes, no assets are used.

Generative parameters include density of elements, parameters of elements and color. 

Thank you so much for collecting!

's' to capture a 6400 x 6400 png with border

'b' to capture a 6400 x 6400 png without border

metadata.name: Annum #6172
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.
